<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Druids vs. Wizards</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Seoman Snowlock[CC-Council]">Seoman Snowlock[CC-Council]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:32 a.m. 26/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Druids vs. Wizards<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1958" TARGET=_self>Druids vs. Wizards</A> (Phazer)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Well...in most duels with a wizard you won't have time to cast a DoT on him until he is out of mana (unless you opt to cast it as your first spell which increases the chances that his offense will overtake your heals later). You won't me using your mana offensively anyways so why pretend :P Heal up as he unloads on you and if you do it right, the wizard will run out of mana without getting you below 2 bubbles of hp and you will even have some mana left over for a couple of swarms as you crack his skull with your club :P

<P>Seo
<BR>ps: it takes a smart wizard to have any chance vs a healer, it takes a semi-competent healer to beat ANY wizard :P
<P>&gt; I was trying a few things with a friend earlier. I found that
<BR>&gt; Wizards tend to have more powerful spells, and can indeed kill a
<BR>&gt; druid with very few problems.
<P>&gt; We were both Level 21, and we started off at the same time. We
<BR>&gt; battled about 2-3 times. I did lose all of the duels, but I
<BR>&gt; believe the reason is because I was unable to use Stinging Swarm
<BR>&gt; (DOT spell) This is because Verant believes it is illeagal, and
<BR>&gt; makes the other opponent lose experiance. Just thought I would
<BR>&gt; let you know, that a Wizard can and does have an advantage over
<BR>&gt; a Druid offensive spell-wise. Perhaps I structured my attack
<BR>&gt; method wrong, but I was simply unable to win. Although the
<BR>&gt; opponents health was nearing death, without DOT we are useless
<BR>&gt; to Wizards.
<P>&gt; Just my opinion, and I COULD be wrong.
<BR>&gt; Phazer
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
